# Deploy email notifications

When you **push to `main`** changes under deploy paths, GitHub Actions runs **Deploy to Vercel** and emails a summary if secrets are configured.

## GitHub secrets (pick one provider)

**Option A — Resend:** `RESEND_API_KEY`, `DEPLOY_NOTIFY_EMAIL`, optional `DEPLOY_FROM_EMAIL`

**Option B — Gmail SMTP (no Resend):** `SMTP_USER`, `SMTP_PASS` (Google App Password), `DEPLOY_NOTIFY_EMAIL`, optional `DEPLOY_FROM_EMAIL`

Resend is preferred when available; SMTP is the fallback when Resend signup/dashboard won't load.

## Agent responsibilities

1. **Commit messages that email well** — notify script includes up to **4 subject lines** from the push.

2. **Push when deploy-worthy** — after push, tell the user deploy is in progress and they'll get an email if secrets exist.

3. **If no push**, say so in chat — email only fires from CI.

4. **On deploy failure**, share the GitHub Actions run URL.

Do not claim an email was sent unless a push triggered the workflow and email secrets are configured.
